cs.HC, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CY 

This paper discusses the usability factors of a multilingual website, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and natural language processing (cs.CL) to ensure that the text is culturally and linguistically appropriate for the users. The study also involves analyzing user satisfaction, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) to identify patterns and trends. Finally, the study recommends the use of graphics in multilingual websites, which can be related to cybersecurity (cs.CY) to ensure the safety and security of the website.
